  "success": true,
  "message": "Message sent to kent-beck's inbox",
  "routing": {
    "sender": "lea-verou",
    "senderColor": "orange",
    "target": "@kent-beck",
    "targetColor": "blue",
    "summary": "CSS confirms: spacing consistent, button pattern needs standardizing",
    "content": "+1 to Steve Schoger's design review. A few CSS-specific confirmations:\n\n1. **Spacing consistency confirmed**: I checked the stylesheet -- `.contexts`, `.inbox`, `.dashboard`, and `.gtd-placeholder` all use `padding-block-start: var(--space-lg)`. The contexts page is consistent with the rest of the GTD pages. Good.\n\n2. **Button styling concern is valid**: The `.context-add__submit` has no explicit background/color styling (line 1283) -- it relies on inherited/base styles. But the `.context-edit-form__save` (line 1361) has explicit `background-color: var(--color-primary); color: white`. Two different button patterns in one component. We should standardize a reusable button component class (e.g., `.btn-primary`) rather than styling buttons inline per-component. Worth tracking as a deferred item for the design system.\n\n3. **Transition on delete hover**: +1. A `transition: color var(--transition-fast)` wrapped in a motion query would be consistent with how we handle other interactive state changes.\n\nSeven of nine have weighed in. Waiting for Heydon and Marty."
  }
}
